-> Defination: 
    It is root class or Parent class of all classes in java
    It is present inside " Java.lang.package. "
    All classes implicitly or explicitly inherit Object class.

-> Methods
    equals(Object obj): Compares the current object with another object for equality.
    hashCode(): Returns a hash code value for the object, which is used in data structures like hash tables.
    toString(): Returns a string representation of the object.
    getClass(): Returns the runtime class of the object.
    clone(): Creates and returns a copy of the object.
    finalize(): Objects created from classes inherit the finalize method from the Object class. This method can be overridden 
    to define custom cleanup actions before an object is garbage collected.
    wait(), notify(), and notifyAll(): Used for synchronization and inter-thread 
